sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Test Client / User
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Kueue as Kueue Controller<br/>Workload Admission
    participant TrainOp as Training Operator v1
    participant TrainerV2 as Kubeflow Trainer v2
    participant JobSet as JobSet Controller
    participant KubeRay as KubeRay Operator
    participant Master as Worker Pod 0 (Master)<br/>Training Runtime Image
    participant Workers as Worker Pod 1..N<br/>Training Runtime Image
    participant RayHead as Ray Head Pod<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant RayWorkers as Ray Worker Pods<br/>10001/TCP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,HF: Flow 1: Distributed PyTorch Training (Training Operator v1)

    Client->>K8sAPI: POST PyTorchJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Kueue: Workload admission check
    Kueue-->>K8sAPI: Workload admitted<br/>(unsuspend job)
    K8sAPI->>TrainOp: PyTorchJob event
    TrainOp->>Master: Create master pod
    TrainOp->>Workers: Create worker pods
    Master->>Workers: NCCL AllReduce<br/>29500/TCP plaintext
    Workers->>S3: Download dataset<br/>HTTPS/443 AWS IAM
    Workers->>HF: Download model<br/>HTTPS/443 HF_TOKEN
    Workers-->>Master: Training gradients<br/>NCCL
    Master->>S3: Upload model checkpoint<br/>HTTPS/443 AWS IAM

    Note over Client,HF: Flow 2: Ray Distributed Training

    Client->>K8sAPI: POST RayCluster + RayJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Kueue: Workload admission check
    Kueue-->>K8sAPI: Workload admitted
    K8sAPI->>KubeRay: RayCluster event
    KubeRay->>RayHead: Create Ray head pod<br/>6379/TCP GCS
    KubeRay->>RayWorkers: Create Ray worker pods
    RayHead->>RayWorkers: Ray protocol<br/>10001/TCP plaintext
    Client->>RayHead: Submit job via Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP<br/>via Route 443/TCP TLS edge
    RayWorkers->>S3: Data I/O<br/>HTTPS/443 AWS IAM
    RayHead-->>Client: Job status/logs<br/>8265/TCP HTTP

    Note over Client,HF: Flow 3: Kubeflow Trainer v2 TrainJob

    Client->>K8sAPI: POST TrainJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>TrainerV2: TrainJob event
    TrainerV2->>JobSet: Create JobSet CR
    K8sAPI->>Kueue: Workload admission
    Kueue-->>K8sAPI: Admitted
    JobSet->>Workers: Create worker pods
    Workers->>Workers: Distributed training<br/>NCCL/Gloo
    Workers->>S3: Store results<br/>HTTPS/443
